wikipedia_page.main: Robert Austin (28 December 1871 – 26 May 1958) was an English cricketer. He played one first-class match for Oxford University Cricket Club in 1894. He was educated at Cheltenham College and Oriel College, Oxford. He became a schoolteacher in England, then moved to South Africa and was headmaster of Parktown Preparatory School in Johannesburg.
